-- Death Toll Reaches 118 in Flooding Across Southern China, Xinhua Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-14T13:57:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/death-toll-reaches-118-in-flooding-across-southern-china-xinhua-reports.html

          
          
             Flooding across south China have
left at least 118 people dead and 47 missing since July 1, the
official Xinhua News Agency said today citing the Civil Affairs
Ministry.  
 More than 32.3 million people in 10 southern provinces and
Chongqing Municipality had been affected by rain and floods,
Xinhua said. About 101,000 houses were destroyed and almost 1.1
million people had been relocated, it said.  
          
          


  


        